cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "Philosophische Entscheidungsanalyse (PDI) — Academic Edition"
abstract: >
  Interactive tool for the systematic analysis of ethical decision
  situations through twelve philosophical traditions. Pluralistic
  structure-comparison approach instead of monistic synthesis.
  Designed for school (Sek. II), university (Bachelor, Master),
  professional practice, and personal reflection. Single-file React
  application with persistent browser storage, four citation styles
  (APA, Harvard, Chicago, MLA), 50+ glossary terms, and cross-tool
  JSON export (konkordanz-v1 schema).
